parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to brake fluid boiling, and potentially resulting in brake failure, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.

wheels feeling hot to the touch
burning smell coming from the rear of the vehicle.
